assert y_test.shape == (10000, 1)

2.3 Baseline model¶

In [ ]:
model_baseline = keras.Sequential([

                Input(shape=(32,32,3)),
                Conv2D(10, kernel_size=(5,5), kernel_initializer=HeUniform(), activation='relu', strides=1),
                MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2),
                
                Conv2D(10, kernel_size=(5,5), kernel_initializer=HeUniform(), activation='relu', strides=1),
                MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2),

                Flatten(),

                Dense(20, activation='relu'),
                Dense(10, activation='softmax')
                
                           
])

model_baseline.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
    loss = losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(),
    metrics=['Accuracy']
)

model_baseline.summary()

model_baseline_fit = model_baseline.fit(
    x=x_train_500,
    y=y_train_500,
    # validation_split=0.2,
    validation_data = (x_test, y_test),
    epochs=10000,
    validation_freq=100,
    batch_size=512,
    verbose =2
)
model_baseline.save_weights("model_baseline_weights.h5")

from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
import plotly.graph_objects as go

fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=("Loss", "Accuracy"))

fig.add_trace(
    go.Scatter(y=model_baseline_fit.history['loss'],
               line_color='red',
               name='Training Loss'
               ),
    row=1, col=1
)
fig.add_trace(
    go.Scatter(y=model_baseline_fit.history['val_loss'],
               x=[i*100 for i in range(len(model_baseline_fit.history['val_loss']))],
               mode='lines+markers',
               line_color='orange',
               name='Testing Loss'
               ),
    row=1, col=1
)
fig.add_trace(
    go.Scatter(y=model_baseline_fit.history['Accuracy'],
               line_color='blue',
               name='Training Accuracy'
               ),
    row=1, col=2
)
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(y=model_baseline_fit.history['val_Accuracy'],
                         x=[i*100 for i in range(len(model_baseline_fit.history['val_Accuracy']))],
                         mode='lines+markers',
               line_color='green',
               name='Testing Accuracy'
               ),
    row=1, col=2
)
fig.update_yaxes(title_text="loss", row=1, col=1)
fig.update_yaxes(title_text="accuracy", row=1, col=2)
fig.update_layout(height=600, width=1300, title_text="HW3:P2.3 CNN baseline model metrics")
fig.show()

baseline_hist = pd.DataFrame(model_baseline_fit.history['Accuracy'], columns=['Accuracy'])
baseline_hist['loss'] =  model_baseline_fit.history['loss']
baseline_hist['val_loss'] =  model_baseline_fit.history['val_loss'] + [np.NAN]*9900
baseline_hist['val_Accuracy'] =  model_baseline_fit.history['val_Accuracy'] + [np.NAN]*9900

baseline_hist.to_csv('baseline_hist.csv')
